fields.name: Complete Blood Count (CBC)
fields.description: Evaluates overall health and detects a wide range of disorders.

fields.name: Lipid Profile
fields.description: Measures cholesterol and triglycerides to assess heart health.

fields.name: Thyroid Function Test
fields.description: Assesses thyroid activity by measuring T3, T4, and TSH levels.

fields.name: Liver Function Test (LFT)
fields.description: Evaluates liver enzymes, proteins, and bilirubin levels to check liver health.

fields.name: Kidney Function Test (KFT)
fields.description: Assesses kidney function by measuring creatinine and urea levels.

fields.name: Blood Glucose Test
fields.description: Measures blood sugar levels to screen for diabetes.

fields.name: Urine Analysis (Routine)
fields.description: Evaluates urine for infections, kidney function, and other abnormalities.

fields.name: Electrolyte Panel
fields.description: Checks sodium, potassium, chloride, and other essential electrolytes.

fields.name: Vitamin D Test
fields.description: Measures serum vitamin D levels to evaluate bone health.

fields.name: C-Reactive Protein (CRP) Test
fields.description: Detects inflammation in the body by measuring CRP levels.

fields.name: HbA1c Test
fields.description: Measures average blood sugar levels over the past 2-3 months.

fields.name: Iron Studies
fields.description: Assesses iron, ferritin, and transferrin levels to evaluate anemia.

fields.name: Rheumatoid Factor (RF) Test
fields.description: Helps in diagnosing rheumatoid arthritis by detecting rheumatoid factor.

fields.name: Prothrombin Time (PT/INR) Test
fields.description: Evaluates blood clotting by measuring prothrombin time and INR.

fields.name: Serum Calcium Test
fields.description: Measures calcium levels to assess bone and kidney function.

fields.name: Serum Uric Acid Test
fields.description: Determines uric acid levels to help diagnose gout and kidney issues.

fields.name: Fasting Insulin Test
fields.description: Assesses insulin levels for evaluating metabolic function.

fields.name: Lipoprotein(a) Test
fields.description: Measures lipoprotein(a) levels associated with heart disease risk.
